{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=July 2016}} {{more footnotes|date=July 2016}} {{Orphan|date=June 2016}} {{Underlinked|date=June 2016}} }}
The '''Boardman Hill Solar Farm''' ''BHSF'' is a 150&nbsp;kW AC [[community solar farm]] project. The Boardman Hill Solar Farm is the first community solar array in [[Vermont]] that fulfills the [http://www.greenenergytimes.net/2015/12/15/a-vermont-grown-vermont-green-solar-farm/ “Vermont Grown, Vermont Green”] mission: complete member-ownership, democratic management of ongoing operations, and retirement of the RECs generated by the solar farm.<ref>http://vtdigger.org/2015/10/27/boardman-hill-solar-farm-in-rutland-has-ribbon-cutting/</ref> It is located on the [https://vtfarmersmarket.org/vendors/boardman-hill-farm/ Boardman Hill Farm] in [[West Rutland, Vermont]].In 2015 it was awarded the [http://www.rutlandherald.com/articles/solar-farm-gains-national-interest/ Vermont Energy and Climate Action Network Best Project of 2015]
'''Project Overview'''
